programme.desc: This programme looks at the Cretaceous period, 106 million years ago. Volcanic activity forces the continents apart, and dinosaurs diversify into a range of species to cope with environmental extremes.

programme.desc: The longest chain of mountains in the world, the Andes run the length of western South America and dictate the climate for the whole continent. They include some of the highest peaks outside the Himalayas.
programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Amazon: One Jungle, Many Worlds
programme.desc: The Amazon is the largest rainforest in the world, and the richest ecosystem on earth. This film uncovers what makes the Amazon such a powerhouse of evolution; how it has come to home a third of all species on the planet.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth
programme.desc: Patagonia is a place of extremes  of vast ice fields and snow-capped mountains; of windswept deserts, and violent oceans. Survival here means being tough enough to cope with brutal winters, and canny enough to exploit brief seasons of plenty.
programme.sub-title: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ngorongoro: Born of Fire
programme.desc: Ngorongoro is thought to have formed about 2.5 million years ago from a large volcano, whose cone collapsed inward after a major eruption. This fertile land is full of wildlife, from cunning hyena and proud lions to vast herds of wildebeest and elephants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Madagascar: Islands of Monsters
programme.desc: Madagascar is truly a weird and wonderful land. Isolated on an island of extreme and magical looking locations, life has adapted and diversified. With few predators, numbers have proliferated and natural selection has gone mad.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Congo: the Untamed Heart
programme.desc: Known for centuries as Africa's Dark Heart, the Congo is a multi-layered, three-dimensional world, seething with innumerable species. By peeling back the layers, we discover how this vast rainforest works, and expose the hidden lives of its inhabitants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice
programme.desc: Mount Kenya soars over 5km into the air. It is the second highest mountain in Africa. At its summit, temperatures fluctuate from over 30 degrees celsius to below freezing.
programme.sub-title: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Namibia: Sands of Time
programme.desc: Namibia is an arid, rough land. However, it has been inhabited for thousands of years, by people as well as animals, and shows no sign of losing popularity with either.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Zambezi: Wild Water
programme.desc: The Zambezi is one of Africa's most influential rivers. It supports some of the continent's most spectacular wildlife. However, the Zambezi's long and winding journey destroys, as well as creates.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.
programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: Christmas in Wonderland
programme.desc: Starring Matthew Knight and Chris Kattan. Three children and their father move from California to Canada. When they go shopping at the mall, they find counterfeit cash, inadvertently help catch crooks, and make a discovery about Santa.

programme.title: Christmas in Mississippi
programme.desc: Photographer Holly returns to Gulfport, Mississippi for Christmas. Their traditional holiday light show has been revived again since a hurricane struck five years earlier. She is shocked to learn the festival is run by her high school sweetheart, Mike.

programme.title: Finding Mrs. Claus
programme.desc: When Mrs. Claus (Mira Sorvino) feels neglected by her less than attentive husband (Will Sasso), she goes to Las Vegas to help a little girl with her Christmas wish.

programme.title: 12 Dogs of Xmas
programme.desc: In this heartwarming sequel to the holiday classic, Emma (Danielle Chuchran) rallies her friends new and old to save a beloved puppy orphanage by putting on a musical holiday extravaganza.

programme.title: The Search for Secret Santa
programme.desc: A reporter tries to uncover and bring closure to a long-lost, undelivered gift before Christmas.

programme.title: Christmas Angel
programme.desc: Christmas wishes made before a long-abandoned house that start coming true lead an elementary schoolgirl to discover a reclusive woman living inside.

programme.title: A Prince and Pauper Christmas
programme.desc: A confidential informant goes missing and a young agent hires a look-a-like to play his role.

programme.title: Wishin' and Hopin'
programme.desc: Based on the New York Times best-selling Christmas novel by Wally Lamb comes the new Christmas classic, starring Molly Ringwald and featuring Chevy Chase as the narrator.

programme.title: A Country Christmas Story
programme.desc: Musical icon and multiple Grammy Award winner Dolly Parton and Grammy Award nominated R&B singer and producer Brian McKnight star in this Lifetime Original Movie.

programme.title: A Christmas Tree Miracle
programme.desc: A warm-hearted Christmas tale to remind us that in the holiday season, the best gifts in life are the simple ones, and that miracles do happen, if you believe.

programme.title: Defending Santa
programme.desc: A small-town sheriff finds a man asleep in the woods who claims to be Santa Claus.

programme.desc: A failed New York playwright awkwardly navigates the transition from Next Big Thing to Last Year's News. Starring: Kristen Wiig, Annette Bening, Matt Dillon, Natasha Lyonne

programme.title: National Lampoon's Gold Diggers
programme.desc: A pair of losers marry two elderly sisters, thinking they'll inherit their fortune and Beverly Hills estate.

programme.title: Olympic Dreams
programme.desc: In this heart-warming romantic comedy, an athlete and volunteer form an unexpected bond at the Olympic Games.

programme.title: How to Murder a Millionaire
programme.desc: Spoiled Beverly Hills housewife Irma Summers is convinced that her husband plans to kill her. She escapes from her mansion with an enterprising con-woman, and the pair soon finds themselves up to their elbows in action, intrigue, and misadventures.

programme.title: Battling for Baby
programme.desc: After Katherine (Courteney Cox) decides to return to work to help pay the bills, her baby's grandmothers (Debbie Reynolds & Suzanne Pleshette) argue over who will take care of her child.

programme.title: You Stupid Man
programme.desc: A writer struggles to deal with the break-up with his girlfriend. It does not help with getting her out of his mind that she recently became a famous TV start.

programme.title: Scorched
programme.desc: In this crime caper set in a small deserted town, three mischievous bank employees all plan to rob the bank at the same time but they're unaware of what the others are up to. But needless to say, it's all a bit of a botched job!

programme.title: Bottle Shock
programme.desc: The story of the early days of California wine making featuring the now infamous, blind Paris wine tasting of 1976 that has come to be known as "Judgment of Paris". Feat: Chris Pine, Alan Rickman & Bill Pullman.

programme.title: Look Who's Talking
programme.desc: If you've always wanted to know what a baby thinks of the world around him, you finally have your chance. With Bruce Willis supplying the voice of Mikey's thoughts, this is one baby who says exactly what's on his mind. Rating: PG-13

programme.title: Myth Hunters
programme.desc: Richard Knight, an actor and laborer, became obsessed with Captain Kidd's treasure. He found clues in old maps and located a potential site in Communist Vietnam's Hon Tre Lon. Despite risks, he and Fred Graham journeyed there, only to be captured.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Does the Bible contain hidden messages encoded within certain passages of the Old Testament? Is the prophetic nature of these 'codes' proof the Bible's author is of supernatural or extraterrestrial origin?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard interviews the expedition organizer who is planning on leading a team of scientists, filmmakers and tourists to the Arctic aboard a Russian nuclear ice-breaker in search of an entrance into the interior of our world.
programme.sub-title: Journey to the Center of the Earth

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard meets members of the 9/11 Truth movement who challenge the official version of events concerning the attack on the U.S. Pentagon. Researchers present evidence to suggest the attack was perpetrated by some rogue element inside the U.S. government.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims that the supposed mastermind behind the 9/11 terrorist attacks and leader of the Al Qaeda terrorist cell remained a CIA asset until his death.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard speaks with two investigative journalists and a natural health practitioner who maintain vaccines are neither safe nor effective.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Can radiation from electrical appliances, power lines, microwave ovens, and wireless technology such as cell phones, baby monitors, alter our DNA, and cause illnesses?
programme.sub-title: The Dangers of EMF (Electro Magnetic Frequencies)

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Alien Abductions
programme.desc: Richard speaks with two alleged alien abductees about their claims they were taken aboard an alien space craft.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: For centuries, farmers have been discovering strange, complex geometric patterns comprised of rings, circles and other intricate shapes in their fields.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard meets the owners of an abnormal humanoid skull allegedly discovered in Mexico in the 1930s and a researcher who has had the skull subjected to numerous tests including carbon-14 dating, and DNA in order to determine it’s origin.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Mystery of Oak Island
programme.desc: Richard investigates Canada's best-known mysteries, the Oak Island treasure. Also known as the money pit, the site has become one of the world's deepest and most costly archaeological digs.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Energy Healing
programme.desc: Several energy healers claim they are able to produce spontaneous miraculous healing through a laying on of hands. Claims of similar such healing by a man in a remote village in Brazil, known as John of God are also examined.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Execution of MLK and The Framing of James Earl Ray
programme.desc: In this re-examination of the assassination of civil rights leader Martin Luther King, Richard meets several researchers who provide evidence that the convicted gunman, James Earl Ray was not the real triggerman.
programme.sub-title: The Execution of MLK and The Framing of James Earl Ray

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Birthers - Obama's Birth Certificate
programme.desc: Richard interviews several prominent 'Birthers' who present evidence that proves Barack Obama is not eligible to be President because he does not meet the qualifications of a natural born citizen.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: RFID Chips
programme.desc: Could implantable RFID chips or Radio-frequency identification tags currently in widespread use in retail industry be used to surreptitiously track and control people?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Assassination of John Lennon
programme.desc: The Conspiracy Show travels to New York, LA and Toronto in order to investigate the murder of John Lennon. Several researchers posit that Lennon's supposed killer Mark David Chapman was either a patsy or a mind-controlled assassin.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Did Jim Morrison Fake His Death?
programme.desc: Is it conceivable that the Doors legendary front man did not die in a bathtub in Paris of an apparent drug overdose?
programme.sub-title: Did Jim Morrison Fake His Death?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Water Engine
programme.desc: Did the late Stanley Meyer figure out a way to run an internal combustion engine on pure water? And was he murdered because of the threat his invention posed to Big Oil?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Murder of Marilyn Monroe
programme.desc: Did this pop icon and blond bombshell succumb to a drug overdose in 1962 as we've been led to believe or was she killed for 'knowing too much?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Is The Cure for Cancer Being Suppressed?
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims that the medical profession, drug companies, the food industry and government agencies are suppressing a cure for cancer.
programme.sub-title: Is The Cure for Cancer Being Suppressed?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Bilderbergs
programme.desc: A glimpse backstage at the highly secretive annual gathering of the world's richest and most powerful movers and shakers.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Shroud of Turin
programme.desc: Is this famous piece of linen cloth the actual burial cloth of Jesus Christ or a clever Medieval hoax?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Fake Arab Spring?
programme.desc: Who was really behind a series of revolts, protests, and uprisings that swept the Middle East starting in late 2010?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Ouija Boards?
programme.desc: Harmless board game or portal to the spirit world? Richard delves into the history and folklore of 'talking boards' with a collector of Ouija boards and a world renowned paranormal investigator.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Global Warming, A Hoax?
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several journalists and researchers who argue the theory that human use of carbon-based fossil fuels will lead to catastrophic global warming.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: JFK
programme.desc: Richard meets with some prominent JFK assassination researchers to discuss the November 1963 murder of President John F. Kennedy.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Pterodactyls
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several explorers and cryptozoologists who believe pterodactyls, flying dinosaurs thought to have become extinct some 60 million years ago, are alive and thriving in remote places such as Papua New Guinea.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: GMO - Genetically Modified Food
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims crop plants created for human or animal consumption using the latest molecular biology techniques are unsafe.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Fluoride
programme.desc: The Conspiracy Show investigates the safety and efficacy of putting fluoride in our water supply. Dentists say that putting fluoride in the water supply prevents tooth decay, but some researchers claim it's a toxic substance that causes cancer.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Area 51
programme.desc: What's going on inside Area 51, America's most carefully guarded secret? The mysterious military base located 30 minutes north west of Las Vegas has been rumored to be involved in back engineering advanced alien technology recovered from UFO crash sites.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Remote Viewing
programme.desc: We meet several individuals who claim they have the ability to transcend time and space and identify people, objects, and locations hidden from their view.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Freemasons
programme.desc: Are the Freemasons a harmless fraternity whose members busy themselves by raising money for children's hospitals or a satanic cult whose tentacles and enslave mankind?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Depopulation Agenda
programme.desc: Richard interviews an investigative health reporter and a NY Times best-selling author about their claims that a powerful cabal is waging war on mankind through forced sterilization, vaccination and other means.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Mokele Mbembe
programme.desc: Mokele Mbembe means able to stem the flow of rivers. The Pygmies there say they have encountered just such a creature and according to their descriptions, this behemoth is a dead ringer for an Apotosaurus.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Bigfoot
programme.desc: Two prominent Bigfoot trackers and a cryptozoologist affirm the existence of this shy and elusive creature and relate several close encounters with Sasquatch.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Uffizi Gallery, Florence
programme.desc: From a famous artist who vanished to a traitorous Nazi who saved the day, discover the secrets inside the Uffizi Gallery.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Kunsthistorisches Museum, Vienna
programme.desc: From the alchemy of turning silver into gold to a dance craze that changed history, discover the secrets inside the Kunsthistorisches Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Natural History Museum, London
programme.desc: From Darwin’s original specimens to a lost workshop that inspired James Bond, discover the secrets of Britain’s Natural History Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Natural History Museum, London

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the National Museum of Anthropology, Mexico City
programme.desc: From ancient athletes who kick a severed head to a peasant dress that brings down an empire, discover the secrets inside the National Museum of Anthropology.
programme.sub-title: Inside the National Museum of Anthropology, Mexico City

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Pergamon and Neues Museums, Berlin
programme.desc: From Vikings who break unbreakable swords to curators who solve the world’s hardest jigsaw puzzle, discover the secrets inside the Pergamon and Neues Museums.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Pergamon and Neues Museums, Berlin

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the National Archeological Museum of Athens
programme.desc: From a dodgy archeologist who discovers a golden mask to an ancient gadget that reveals the future, discover the secrets inside the National Archaeological Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the National Archeological Museum of Athens

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside The ROM, Toronto
programme.desc: From a medieval hand-grenade to an extremely rare dinosaur, discover the secrets inside the Royal Ontario Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the State Historical Museum, Moscow
programme.desc: From the duel that killed a genius to Lenin’s Rolls-Royce, discover the secrets inside the State Historical Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the State Historical Museum, Moscow

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Metropolitan Museum, New York
programme.desc: From the mystery of a king’s madness to a silver chalice some think is the Holy Grail, discover the secrets inside the Metropolitan Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Metropolitan Museum, New York

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Palacio Real, Madrid
programme.desc: From a clock that runs on witchcraft to a 21st Century king who outfoxes a fascist, discover the secrets inside the Palacio Real.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Egyptian Museum
programme.desc: From the mystery of a Pharaoh’s gold to the strange practice of animal mummification, discover the secrets inside the Egyptian Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the American Museum of Natural History, New York
programme.desc: From a dinosaur embryo that solves a murder mystery to a spacecraft catching a comet’s tail, discover the secrets inside the American Museum of Natural History.
programme.sub-title: Inside the American Museum of Natural History, New York

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Israel Museum, Jerusalem
programme.desc: From a scientist who recreates the crucifixion to an ancient amulet that proves Star Trek's Spock is Jewish, discover the secrets inside the Israel Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the State Hermitage Museum
programme.desc: From ancient mummies who sport tattoos to re-examining who really killed Rasputin, discover the secrets inside the State Hermitage Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Smithsonian Institution, Washington DC
programme.desc: From the Zeros that bombed Pearl Harbor to the rocket that could take humans to Mars, discover the secrets inside the Smithsonian Institution.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Smithsonian Institution, Washington DC

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Imperial War Museum, London
programme.desc: From Churchill risking his life in the Blitz to 21st Century soldiers who become invisible, discover the secrets inside the Imperial War Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Imperial War Museum, London

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Vatican
programme.desc: From Michelangelo’s Sistine Chapel frescoes to the fall of the Knights Templar, discover the secrets inside the Vatican Museums.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Topkapi Palace Museum, Istanbul
programme.desc: From assassins who plot to poison a Sultan to bitter enemies who sign the world’s first peace treaty, discover the secrets inside the Topkapi Palace Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Topkapi Palace Museum, Istanbul

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Chateau of Versailles, Paris
programme.desc: From the schemes of Marie Antoinette to the spectrum of a star that reveals the origin of human life, discover the secrets inside the Chateau of Versailles.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Chateau of Versailles, Paris

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MANMADE
programme.desc: When it comes to disasters, mother nature has mankind beat. However, as mankind expands, evolves and technology advances, it comes with dangerous challenges. When errors are made or unforeseen circumstances occur, the results can be devastating.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: TORNADO
programme.desc: A tornado is a violently rotating column of air extending from the base of a thunderstorm down to the ground. Tornadoes are capable of completely destroying well-made structures, uprooting trees, and hurling objects through the air like deadly missiles.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MEGAFLOODS
programme.desc: Water covers two thirds of the earth’s surface, and we are utterly dependent on it, but when this vital ingredient of life unleashes its fury on the planet it becomes the ultimate bringer of death.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: EARTHQUAKES
programme.desc: Earthquakes happen when tectonic plates suddenly slip causing shock waves to shake the surface of the Earth. They occur on fault lines - the most active are the Ring of Fire in the Pacific Ocean and the San Andreas fault on America’s west coast.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: CONSTRUCTION
programme.desc: Bridges and tunnels have transformed the way we live, making the inaccessible easy to reach, and turning time consuming journeys into convenient commutes, but when things go wrong they can go very wrong indeed.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: AIR, LAND AND SEA
programme.desc: Planes, trains and ships, our mass transit systems, have had a profound effect on mankind, making the world smaller and more connected.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: HURRICANES
programme.desc: Hurricanes, Typhoons and Cyclones all the same thing with different names – what they also have in common is their destructive power! Hurricanes are large, swirling storms and winds from a hurricane can damage buildings or trees.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: VOLCANOES
programme.desc: Volcanoes are Earth’s geologic architects. They’ve created more than 80 percent of our planet’s surface and their explosive force has crafted both mountains and craters.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Wild Weather Season
programme.desc: 2005 seemed to be the year that Earth went wild. Follow George as he brings us back to the site of his hairiest adventures from that year.

programme.title: Angry Planet: West Coast Winter Weather
programme.desc: On Canada's rugged West Coast, George ice-climbs a frozen waterfall, uses ski-skins to climb Mt.Garibaldi to an alpine lake, visits a storm-watching lodge on British Columbia's Long Beach, home of winter surfing and massive Pacific storms.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Waterspouts
programme.desc: In the Florida Keys, George uses a motorboat, a van and small plane to get up close to waterspouts - the nautical cousins of tornadoes. He also meets some of the 25 million alligators that live in the Sunshine State.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Island Caving
programme.desc: Accompanied by a group of hardcore cavers from Alberta and British Columbia, George descends into spectacular caves that lead deep into the earth on Vancouver Island. The team carries inflatable kayaks to explore a dark underground river.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Desert Monsoon
programme.desc: Enlisting the help of fellow storm chaser R.J. Evans, George heads to Arizona to photograph spectacular lightning storms triggered by the desert monsoon season. R.J. however is known as "America's noisiest athiest" for his free-thought radio show.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Polynesian Volcanoes
programme.desc: In New Zealand, George learns that an undersea volcano 1000 miles North in Tonga is creating a new island. After nautical mishaps, clad in nothing but underwear and a life jacket, George becomes one of the first explorers on this new land.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Java: Land of Fire
programme.desc: In the Pacific Ring of Fire island of Java, George explores new ash eruptions from Anak Krakatau, whose 1883 eruption shook the world. He travels to Merapi and descends into Kawah Ijen to explore the world's largest lake of sulfuric acid.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Highway to Hail
programme.desc: George and his team head into "bears' cage", looking to get beat up by the biggest, baddest hailstones in Texas and Oklahoma. Their storm chasing vehicles don't look too pretty after coming through these massive storms.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Costa Rica
programme.desc: George explores the volcanoes of Costa Rica with an international team of scientists, rafts down white water rivers in full flood, rappels down raging waterfalls, and handles some of deadliest snakes this tropical country has to offer.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Winds Of Autumn
programme.desc: This year he starts off by getting prepared in a wind tunnel, then he and his chase partner Mark Robinson head to Newfoundland for more wild weather action. Then, it's off to another encounter where the wild wind fans a raging inferno.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Iceland: Fire and Ice

programme.title: World's Greatest: Timeless Cities & Towns
programme.desc: These cities and towns are special places where the past coexists with the present, creating cultures totally unique to their people and their part of the world and adhering to ancient traditions and while introducing modern innovations.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Capital Cities
programme.desc: With visionaries, politicians, and activists, these metropolises are defined as the official seats of government. Dublin, Washington, and Taipei share broad avenues, museums, and monuments, but are as varied as the countries they represent.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Archipelagos
programme.desc: The romantic notion of island life has always attracted us. Explore the histories, cultures, and unique ways of life on the World’s Greatest Archipelagos - clusters of islands that share common bonds of geography, geology, and genealogy.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Battle of Midway (June 2, 1942)
programme.desc: Only one isolated atoll prevents an enemy invasion of Hawaii. Midway Island is where the Japanese fleet converges on a tiny American base with a massive strafing and bombing attack.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Fall of the Philippines
programme.desc: Examining the Japanese invasion of the Philippines in December 1941.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Pearl Harbor (December 7, 1941)
programme.desc: During a two-hour surprise attack on the American Pacific fleet anchored at Pearl Harbor, Japanese navy pilots score a near-complete victory.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Fall of Singapore (October 1941)
programme.desc: Before the sneak attack on Pearl Harbor, the Japanese initiate the Pacific War by firing on the British in Malaya. Their route to the rubber-rich nation takes them into Singapore, the World's most armed fortress.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Battle of Malta (June 1941)
programme.desc: In 1941, Mussolini desperately wants to wrest the tiny island of Malta from the British for control of the Mediterranean. When his inadequate air force fails to bomb the Maltese into submission, Hitler's Luftwaffe joins the campaign.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Operation Mercury
programme.desc: After British forces withdrew in defeat from Greece to the island of Crete in early 1941, they were soon fighting German invasion armies again. This time, 5,000 of Hitler's elite paratroopers landed to complete their conquest in the Mediterranean.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Tobruk
programme.desc: German field marshal Erwin Rommel scores a major victory at the Libyan seaport of Tobruk.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Bombing of England (Fall 1940)
programme.desc: After invading France, Hitler is planning to cross the Channel. His only obstacle is the Royal Air Force. Throughout the summer of 1940, both sides lose an incredible number of daring flyers.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Battle of Norway (Early 1940)
programme.desc: Early in the war, the Germans decide they need to guarantee access to the Norwegian port of Narvik to ensure their supplies of Swedish iron ore. The British, however, send destroyers to up-end the German plan.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Fall of Poland
programme.desc: German tanks roll into Poland in September 1939.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Dunkirk (September 1, 1939)
programme.desc: To keep France free, 400,000 English soldiers have manned the battlefields. Germany's strength is too great and pushes the British to the coast town of Dunkirk.

programme.title: Rommel: The Soldier, The Son, and Hitler
programme.desc: Never a member of the Nazi party, Rommel detested blending politics and war. He would quickly discover that both were always in play under Hitler.

programme.title: VE Day - Forever in their Debt
programme.desc: Tells the stories of those who experienced the end of the war in all its many forms. It features a wide range of interviews from children who remember the street parties, to the servicemen who remember not having to buy a single drink that day.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Building The Brand
programme.desc: Hitler’s fascination with propaganda was born in the trenches of the First World War. There he saw it emerge as a potent tool of psychological warfare - one that he would harness to build the Nazi movement. Witness Hitler's early propaganda tactics.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Power and Persuasion
programme.desc: This episode explores Hitler's approach to propaganda in power; where persuasion was achieved through propaganda and terror, all in service of one goal: the creation of a state under one shared ideology. A new German power fueled by propaganda.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Why We Fight
programme.desc: This episode explores the way Hitler used propaganda to justify his warmongering, reframing it as defense of Germany’s people and borders. It investigates the role propaganda played for both Hitler and the Allies to mobilize their countries for war.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Tragic Sinking of Leopoldville
programme.desc: On the 24th of December 1944, 2 237 American soldiers of the 66th Infantry Division are aboard the Steamer Léopoldville.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: Secret Bunkers of Omaha Beach
programme.desc: On June 6th 1944, Lieutenant-colonel Rudder’s Rangers company climbs the cliffs of the Pointe du Hoc in Normandy with the mission to destroy the German cannons.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Last Flight of the B-17
programme.desc: Twenty-six metres beneath the waves at the foot of the majestic Calvi Citadel in Corsica lies an American plane from the Second World War.
programme.sub-title: The Last Flight of the B-17

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Lost Tanks of D-Day
programme.desc: In Normandy, June 6, 1944, a dozen Sherman tanks equipped with floats, the famous Duplex Drives (DD), leave their ship to swim to Omaha Beach... not all of them make it.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: A Terrible Precedent
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: Arsenal of Democracy
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Rise of The Bomber
programme.desc: Rise of the Bomber: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: War Without Boundaries
programme.desc: War Without Boundaries: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The Means To Victory
programme.desc: The Means to Victory: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain as the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: The World At War
programme.desc: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: By Night & By Day
programme.desc: By Night & By Day: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Bomber: Terror of WWII: Terror of The World
programme.desc: Terror of the World: The story of a deadly war that intertwines Germany, Poland, Japan, Italy and Spain, and the remorseless development of weapons and bombers.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.
programme.sub-title: The Quest for the Holy Grail

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Into the Mountains (Tibet)
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Cro Magnon
programme.desc: The debate about humanity's true origins becomes a nefarious fixation as SS leader Heinrich Himmler turns his attention to proving the Paleolithic past of Germany's Aryan race.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Runes
programme.desc: Runes are the letters of an ancient Germanic writing system that harkens back to a mythological age filled with heroes, magic, and mystery.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Royal Journey
programme.desc: A documentary account of the five-week visit of Princess Elizabeth and the Duke of Edinburgh to Canada and the United States in the fall of 1951.

programme.title: The Fate Of America
programme.desc: On Sept 13, 1759, the Battle of the Plains of Abraham sealed America's fate in 20 mins. 'The Fate of America' explores this myth, leaving French Canadians pondering defeat. Filmmaker Jacques Godbout's take unites Montcalm and Wolfe's descendants.

programme.title: Neighbours Voisins
programme.desc: Two neighbours live side by side in harmony until a flower grows on the dividing line between their properties. Who does it belong to? The argument that follows ends up with both neighbours in their graves. The most famous of Norman McLaren’s films.

programme.title: Twenty Years Of Feminist Filmmaking
programme.desc: A clip montage for presentation at the National Action Committee on the Status of Women to commemorate the 20th anniversary of Studio D and the National Action Committee.

programme.title: Mother Earth/La Terre Notre Mere
programme.desc: Mother Earth is a short, evocative, poetic film that celebrates life on our planet. This documentary film looks at the reality of human beings; the earth is our home and we are profoundly connected to all other beings.

programme.title: Le Grand Serpent Du Monde
programme.desc: A young forty-something, Tom Paradise refuses to grow up. Behind the wheel of his bus he drives endlessly through the city, tracing out the path of his life, dreaming of the landscape of the American West that forever impressed him

programme.title: Corral
programme.desc: A portrait of a cowboy rounding up wild horses, lassoing one of the high-spirited animals in the corral, and then going for a glorious plunging ride across the visually spectacular Rocky Mountain foothills in Alberta.

programme.title: Walking
programme.desc: Ryan Larkin's "Walking" captures various walking styles through line drawing and color wash techniques. It humorously portrays youth's springy steps, high-heeled minces, and elderly ambles, accompanied by unique sound.

programme.title: Doctor Lawyer Indian Chief
programme.desc: A tribute to Indigenous women everywhere, this short documentary focuses on 5 women from across Canada. They talk about the importance of Indigenous culture in helping them to develop a sense of self and seeing through rough times.

programme.title: Abortion Stories From North And South
programme.desc: This film provides a historical overview of how church, state and the medical establishment have determined policies concerning abortion.

programme.title: Turnaround A Story Of Recovery
programme.desc: Turnaround: A Story of Recovery" follows five women battling addiction at Aurora House. This documentary offers insight for families, friends, and professionals interested in alternative treatment methods.

programme.title: Alphee Of The Stars
programme.desc: Alphée of the Stars puts the spotlight on a most unusual girl. With patience and tenderness, a father – who believes in schools that embrace diversity and do not discriminate – challenges our assumptions and reveals an unknown world.

programme.title: Gurdeep Singh Bains
programme.desc: Gurdeep is a thirteen-year-old Canadian Sikh whose family runs a dairy farm near Chilliwack, British Columbia. They have retained their language and religion. Sometimes he feels a little different from the other children because he wears a turban.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Wings On Her Shoulder
programme.desc: This is a 1943 recruitment film. Although it specifically promises women jobs in post-war aviation, its primary message is that women fulfill support positions "so that men might fly.

programme.title: Children Of War
programme.desc: A remarkable documentary in which teenagers from war-torn countries, filmed in interaction with Canadian high-school students, speak with dignity, maturity and candor about the struggles of their people and the suffering they have endured.

programme.title: Sea Dream
programme.desc: Children, like adults, have days that go wrong. This film shows how one little girl overcomes the day's frustrations by diving into an underwater fantasy where she spends time with her friend, the lady octopus.

programme.title: Beautiful Lennard Island
programme.desc: Steven Holland, age ten, is the son of the lighthouse-keeper in charge of Lennard Island, a tiny place west of Vancouver Island. He takes us on a tour and dispels any ideas we might have that living in isolation is boring.

programme.title: Bobs Birthday
programme.desc: Surprise birthday parties can be risky. Especially when the guest of honour is turning 40! When Margaret plans a celebration for her husband, Bob, she underestimates the sudden impact of middle age on his mood.

programme.title: Cry Of The Wild
programme.desc: To hear Bill Mason tell about the making of this feature film (he is also the narrator) is to share with him his affection for his camera-quarry: the big northern timber wolves and pure-white Arctic wolves.

programme.title: Goddess Remembered
programme.desc: This poetic documentary is a salute to 35 000 years of "pre-history," to the values of ancestors only recently remembered, and to the goddess-worshipping religions of the ancient past.

programme.title: Burning Times, The
programme.desc: This film is an in-depth look at the witch-hunts that swept through Europe just a few hundred years ago. False accusations and trials led to massive torture and burnings at the stake, and ultimately to the destruction of an organic way of life.

programme.title: Hometown Holiday
programme.desc: Opposites attract when hometown girl Kristen meets L.A. lawyer Ryan Roarke, but in a case of mistaken identity, this pair is in for quite a romantic rollercoaster.

programme.title: Dashing Home For Christmas
programme.desc: Emily Nichols' detoured holiday travels steer her straight into romance, where she finds out that her calculated plans take a backseat to love.

programme.title: Christmas in the Highlands
programme.desc: Blair Henderson, a perfume expert from New York is sent by her boss to remote Scotland to find a rare Scottish fragrance, The Heart of the Highlands. But when she arrives, she finds the handsome license owner, is a stubborn aristocrat who won’t sell.

programme.title: Homegrown Christmas
programme.desc: After leaving her dream job, Maddie returns home for the holidays to reflect. She reconnects with her high school sweetheart, Carter, sparking tensions. Tasked with organizing a Christmas dance, they set aside differences and rekindle old feelings.

programme.title: Christmas in Washington
programme.desc: EMILY is thrilled when she gets the gig of a lifetime decorating the grand Kalmar Embassy for the festive season. But the new ambassador MAGNUS has no time for Christmas. With some encouragement Emily shows Magnus how magical Christmas can really be.

programme.title: A Christmas to Cherish
programme.desc: Darcy and Aiden are saddened by the imminent closure of their community center. In order to save their beloved center, and with it the Holiday spirit, they embark on a journey, where an unexpected guest unites everyone for the holidays.

programme.title: Looking For Her
programme.desc: When her family guilt-trips her into going home for the holidays and bringing her girlfriend along, perfectionist Taylor concedes, but there's one little problem: they broke up.

programme.title: The Christmas Planner
programme.desc: Type-A Ava owns Rent-an-Elf. This year, she’s hired by newly-single Liam and falls for him and his adorable son Nathan. But just as Ava thinks she’s found her match, Liam’s ex-wife returns, wanting to patch things up.

programme.title: Christmas in Paris
programme.desc: Lucas, a wealthy French entrepreneur, heads to Montana for a very attractive business proposal. When there he meets Robin, falls in love, and whisks her away to Paris on a whirlwind Christmas Adventure. But will business bring an end to this romance?

programme.title: Loving Christmas

programme.title: Eine Hochzeit an Weihnachten

programme.title: Das perfekte Weihnachten
programme.desc: Benjamin will mit seiner Musikkarriere endlich richtig durchstarten und gibt dafür seine Aufnahmen dem Rapper J-Jizzy. Doch zunächst muss Benjamin sich noch seinem Job als Weihnachtsmann in einem Einkaufszentrum widmen...

programme.title: Weihnachtswunderland
programme.desc: Die Weihnachtszeit in New York ist für die erfolglose Künstlerin Heidi Neill alles andere als wundervoll.

programme.title: Weihnachten in der Holly Lane
programme.desc: Die Kindheitsfreundinnen Sarah, Riley und Cat kehren als Erwachsene in ihre Heimatstadt zurück und erinnern sich an die glücklichen Weihnachtsfeste, die sie gemeinsam verbrachten. Sie wollen den Weihnachtszauber von früher wieder zum Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Die Weihnachtstruppe
programme.desc: Die arbeitslose Kunstlehrerin Allie möchte Witwer Gordon und seine Töchter wieder für Weihnachten begeistern.

programme.title: Return To Christmas Creek
programme.desc: Eine junge Chefin kehrt in ihre Heimatstadt zurück, um die Bedeutung von Weihnachten wiederzuentdecken.

programme.title: Christmas in Boston
programme.desc: Gina und Seth sind seit ihrer Kindheit Brieffreunde, haben sich aber noch nie getroffen. Als sie sich endlich dazu entschließen, sich zu treffen, braucht es allerdings ein wenig Weihnachtszauber, um ihre Liebe füreinander aufzudecken.

programme.title: Ich bin nicht bereit für Weihnachten
programme.desc: Hollys energiegeladenes, karriereorientiertes Leben gerat vollig aus den Fugem, als sie feststellt, dass sie nicht mehr lugen kann, weil der Weihnachtsmann ihrer Nichte Anna einen besonderen Wunsch erfullt hat.

programme.title: Weihnachten auf königliche Art
programme.desc: Kristin Cooper, die hübsche und talentierte Assistentin einer globalen PR-Firma, wird mit der Leitung der jährlichen Weihnachtsmodenschau und -auktion für den Bekleidungsunternehmer Mr. Carson beauftragt.

programme.title: Christmas Land
programme.desc: Christmas Land hat seit dem tragischen Tod von Glinda schon bessere Tage gesehen, und Jules muss viele komplizierte Entscheidungen treffen.

programme.title: Mr. Miracle

programme.title: Weihnachten mit Hindernissen
programme.desc: Vicky und Jason haben sich schon längst getrennt. Aber ihre beiden Kinder bringen sie dazu, die Weihnachtsferien gemeinsam zu verbringen. Als dann auch noch Vickys Boss und Jasons Assistentin auftauchen, wird es immer turbulenter...

programme.title: Die Geschichte vom Weihnachtsengel
programme.desc: Eddie und sein Bruder möchten Weihnachten mit ihrer Mutter verbringen, die aber seit einem Autounfall schwer verletzt im Krankenhaus liegt. Eines Nachts träumt Eddie von seiner Mutter, die ihn darum bittet, einen Engel zu finden, damit sie...

programme.title: Die Nanny
programme.desc: Fran hofft auf ein Wunder, als Maxwell, Grace und C.C. nach einem Autounfall vermisst werden.

programme.title: Die Nanny

programme.title: Hallo, ich bin der Weihnachtsmann!
programme.desc: Nachdem der Weihnachtsmann aus seinem Schlitten fällt und eine Amnesie erleidet, kann ihn nur die Unschuld eines kleinen Kindes retten.

programme.title: Weihnachten mit der Familie - Überleben ist alles
programme.desc: Zwei Schwestern und ihre Familien verbringen die Feiertage im elterlichen Landhaus, das in schlechtem Zustand ist. Zwischenmenschliche Probleme eskalieren und der beschauliche Weihnachts-Trip wird zum Alptraum.

programme.title: Freezing Cold Fails

programme.title: Ready for Christmas?

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Weihnachtsstress

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Stille Nacht, heilige Nacht
programme.desc: Kurz vor Weihnachten willigt Buffalo Airways ein, die kanadische Polizei dabei zu unterstützen, Spielzeug und andere Geschenke in die entlegensten Regionen des Landes zu transportieren.

programme.title: The Hills
programme.desc: Lauren, Heidi, Jason und Jordan sind bereit für die Ferien und vor allem die Parties an den Weihnachtsfeiertagen. Natürlich läuft aber nicht alles so gut wie geplant, denn Lauren und Jason haben auf der Silvesterparty einen riesigen Streit...

programme.title: Mrs. Miracle – Ein Zauberhaftes Kindermädchen

programme.title: PAA Christmas
programme.desc: People Are Awesome Christmas edition.

programme.title: The Loud House: Ein Clown für alle Fälle / Der Schneefrei-Horror
programme.desc: Lincoln wird Luans Assistent für ihre Auftritte als Geburtstagsclown. Doch leider haben die beiden nicht den gleichen Humor. // Die Schule ist wegen zu viel Schnee geschlossen. Doch Lisa will das um jeden Preis verhindern.
programme.sub-title: Ein Clown für alle Fälle / Der Schneefrei-Horror

programme.title: iCarly: Ein Schrottbaum zu Weihnachten
programme.desc: Um Weihnachten etwas aufzupeppen baut Spencer einen unkonventionellen Weihnachtsbaum, der versehentlich Feuer fängt und alle Geschenke verbrennt. Craly ist enttäuscht und wünscht sich einen normalen Bruder.

programme.title: SpongeBob Schwammkopf: SpongeBobs Weihnachten
programme.desc: SpongeBob hilft versehentlich Plankton bei seinem Plan, dass die Einwohner Bikini Bottoms auf die "freche" Liste zu setzen. Der Weihnachtsmann muss Plankton stoppen, bevor er seinen Weihnachstwunsch bekommt.

programme.title: Rabbids: Invasion
programme.desc: Die Rabbids wollen weihnachtliche Stimmung schaffen und schmücken eine Palme am Strand. // Ein Rabbid freundet sich mit einem Stück Seife an. // Ein Rabbid gerät in eine Gruppe trotteliger Bankräuber.
programme.sub-title: Herbei, oh ihr Rabbids // Eine glitschige Angelegenheit // Rabbid-Banküberfall

programme.title: Danny Phantom: Der Weihnachtsspuk
programme.desc: Danny hasst Weihnachten. Als Danny versehentlich die einzige Kopie einer Weihnachtsgeistergeschichte zerstört, verwandelt ihn der Autor des Buches in die Hauptfigur einer neuen Weihnachtsgeschichte.

programme.title: Team Umizoomi: Hilfe für den Weihnachtsmann
programme.desc: Es ist Weihnachten, und der Weihnachtsmann braucht dringend Hilfe: Seine Spielzeug-Maschine ist kaputt! Das Team muss schnell handeln und Weihnachten retten.

programme.title: Rocket Power: Schneefrei / Willkommen im Club
programme.desc: Die Kids sollen zu einer langweiligen Schulversammlung. Kurzerhand beschließen sie, dass heute schneefrei ist. / Die Kinder haben eine Probewoche im piekfeinen Ocean Shores Beach Club gewonnen! Ob das gut geht ...?!

programme.title: Game Shakers: Weihnachten mit Reggae Potato
programme.desc: Double G tritt als Reggae Potato mit einem Weihnachts-Special live im Fernsehen auf, aber als die Sendung losgeht, fangen seine Haare Feuer und die Game Shakers müssen für ihn einspringen.

programme.title: Sanjay & Craig: Rettet den Kuscheltag!
programme.desc: Durch eine Dummheit verderben Sanjay und Craig der ganzen Stadt das alljährliche Kuscheltags-Fest. Deshalb machen sich die beiden auf den Weg, um den Kuscheltag zu retten und erleben dabei einige fantastische Überraschungen.

programme.title: Blaze und die Monster-Maschinen: Weihnachten bei den Monster-Maschinen
programme.desc: Blaze hilft dem Weihnachtsmann bei den Vorbereitungen für das große Weihnachtsfest. Doch dann passiert ein kleines Missgeschick, durch das Weihnachten ins Wasser zu fallen droht. Kann Blaze das Fest in letzter Sekunde doch noch retten?!

programme.title: Nickelodeon's Ho Ho Holiday Special: Nickelodeon's Ho Ho Holiday Special
programme.desc: Deine Nickelodeon Stars treffen sich zur besten Weihnachtsparty aller Zeiten. Es geht los mit cooler Musik und lustigen Sketchen, doch bald merken unsere Helden, dass ihnen eine Falle gestellt wurde!

programme.title: Big Time Rush: Big Time Christmas Teil 1
programme.desc: Die Jungs sind zufrieden, zu Weihnachten wieder in Minnesota zu sein, aber Gustavo lässt die anderen nirgendwo los, bis er mit der Aufnahme einer Weihnachtssingle fertig ist. Danny Phantom: Danny Phantom spielt in dieser Animation die Hauptrolle. Es geht

programme.title: Regal Academy: Die Falle der Schneekönigin
programme.desc: Um gegen die sechs großen Märchenfamilien anzukommen, lässt die Schneekönigin Hawks Schwester Fala frei, die sie vor Jahren entführt hat, und benutzt sie als Spielfigur innerhalb der Schule.

programme.title: Little Charmers: Santa Sparkle
programme.desc: Als Hazel die Funkelnacht für alle im Zauberstädtchen ruiniert, hoffen die Zaubersternchen, dass Santa Sparkles Magie alles in Ordnung bringt. Doch kommt wahre Funkelnacht-Magie nicht von innen?

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda: Geschenkte Zeit
programme.desc: Zum jährlichen Winterfestival, hat Po nicht genug Geld, um seinem Dad ein Geschenk zu kaufen. Daher nimmt er einen Job als Kopfgeldjäger an und muss einen gefährlichen, entlaufenen Sträfling einfangen. Doch Po’s Plan verläuft nicht wie erhofft.

programme.title: The Fairly Odd Parents: Fröhliche Wunschnachten!
programme.desc: Timmy bekommt nicht das zu Weihnachten, was er möchte. Also wünscht er es sich einfach. Seine Freunde können das nicht, darum wünscht sich Timmy für alle Kinder einen Zaubergutschein, mit dem sie sich einen Wunsch erfüllen können.

programme.title: SpongeBob Schwammkopf: Weihnachten unter Wasser
programme.desc: Sandy erzählt SpongeBob von Weihnachten und vom Weihnachtsmann. Sponge ist natürlich hellauf begeistert und erzählt in der ganzen Stadt davon. Nun schreiben alle brav ihre Wunschzettel und warten aufs Christkind, nein, den Weihnachtsmann.

programme.title: See Dad Run: Dad und das Weihnachtsgratin
programme.desc: Amy muss am Heiligabend arbeiten und ist darüber so traurig, dass die Familie beschließt, ihr eine ganz besondere Freude zu machen. Dazu müssen David und die Kinder sich allerdings durch einige vorweihnachtliche Hindernisse im Supermarkt kämpfen.

programme.title: Invader Zim: Das schrecklichste Weihnachtsfest aller Zeiten, Teil 1 & Teil 2
programme.desc: Es ist Zims erstes Weihnachtsfest. Als er feststellt, wie fasziniert die Erdlinge vom Weihnachtsmann sind, fasst er einen hinterhältigen Plan: er will selbst in die Rolle des bärtigen alten Mannes schlüpfen.
programme.sub-title: Das schrecklichste Weihnachtsfest aller Zeiten, Teil 1 & Teil 2

programme.title: Regal Academy
programme.desc: Die Freunde müssen sich durch ein mit Fallen durchzogenes Labyrinth kämpfen und ins Schneeschloss gelangen, um die Gefangenen aus den Schneekugeln befreien und zur Regal Academy zurückkehren zu können.

programme.title: Ni Hao, Kai-Lan: Kai-Lans Schnee-Achterbahn
programme.desc: Es hat geschneit und Kai-Lan und ihre Freunde möchten alle zusammen eine Schnee-Achterbahn bauen. Sie bilden kleine Teams und jedes Team übernimmt eine Aufgabe.

programme.title: Robot & Monster: Specknachten
programme.desc: Robot und Monster wollen zusammen mit ihren Familien das Specknachtsfest verbringen. Die Freude ist groß, aber es stellt sich heraus, dass die beiden Familien nichts gemeinsam haben und es kommt zum großen Knall. Sankt Knusprig lenkt ein.

programme.title: Rugrats: Was ist Kwanzaa?
programme.desc: Tante T. stattet Familie Carmichael einen Besuch ab. Gemeinsam wollen sie das afroamerikanische Kwanzaa-Fest feiern.

programme.title: Regal Academy: Weihnachten im Märchenland
programme.desc: Es ist Weihnachten, und Rose freut sich darüber, dass es den Weihnachtsmann wirklich gibt.

programme.title: Rugrats: Im Spielzeugland, Teil 1
programme.desc: Die Babys besuchen mit ihren Eltern das Feriendorf von Stu. Während sich die Erwachsenen in der Western-Holzhütte einsperren, versucht Angelika Santa Clause seinen Job aufzugeben. Können die Rugrats das angerichtete Chaos wieder in Ordnung bringen?

programme.title: Victorious: Die Weihnachtswichtel
programme.desc: Es weihnachtet an der Schauspielschule, und die Freunde müssen die perfekten Wichtelgeschenke füreinander finden. Denn wer das schlechteste Geschenk hat, muss von Tür zu Tür gehen und mit Sikowitz jodeln.

programme.title: Get Blake!: Schnappt euch den Schlafsack! / Schnappt euch die Stiefel!
programme.desc: Die Space-Hörnchen sprühen Roy mit Einschlafspray ein und verschaffen ihm so das verrückteste Date aller Zeiten. // Blake will seine Schuhe kaputtmachen, damit sein Vater ihm Unzerstör-Boots kauft.
programme.sub-title: Schnappt euch den Schlafsack! / Schnappt euch die Stiefel!

programme.title: Hey Arnold: Hitzewelle / Der erste Schnee
programme.desc: Die Stadt wird von einer Hitzewelle erfasst und ein Eisverkäufer, der seine Erfrischungen zu Wucherpreisen an den Mann bringt./Der erste Schnee ist gefallen. Arnold kann es kaum erwarten, hinaus zu gehen und mit seinen Freunden Schlitten zu fahren.

programme.title: T.U.F.F. Puppy: Ein verlorenes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Der etwas schusselige, aber liebenswerte Straßenköter Dudley Puppy muss sich um die Verbrechensbekämpfung in seiner Heimatstadt Petropolis kümmern.

programme.title: Clarissa: Weihnachten im Mai
programme.desc: Natürlich ist Clarissa noch zu jung für den Führerschein. Dennoch kreisen ihre Gedanken einzig und allein um einen 1976er Gremlin, den sie in einer Zeitungsanzeige entdeckt hat.

programme.title: Dora: Fröhliche Weihnachten!
programme.desc: Dora und Boots wollen dem Weihnachtsmann ihrerseits ein Geschenk überreichen. Da sie den Augenblick verpassen, als er die Geschenke für sie abliefert, fahren sie kurz entschlossen mit ihrem Freund Blue Train Richtung Nordpol.

programme.title: Blau und Schlau: Frohe Weihnachten
programme.desc: Alle sind in Ferien- und Festtagsstimmung und bereiten sich auf Weihnachten. Steve spielt 'Blau und Schlau', um herauszufinden, welche Weihnachtserinnerungen Blue wichtig sind.

programme.title: Rocko's Modernes Leben: Fröhliche Weihnachten
programme.desc: Fröhliche Weihnachten: Es weihnachtet sehr - natürlich auch in O-Town. Rocko ist ganz besonders feierlich zumute, weshalb er eine große Party plant.

programme.title: Wonder Pets: Rettet das Rentier!
programme.desc: Linny, Ming-Ming, und Tuck starten zu einer vorweihnachtlichen Rettungsmission: Sie müssen eins der Rentiere des Weihnachtsmanns befreien, das im ewigen Eis am Nordpol feststeckt.

programme.title: Rabbids: Invasion
programme.desc: Ein Rabbid will als Weihnachtsmann die Arktis beglücken. / Ein Rabbid will seine Freunde erschrecken. John versucht, Gina mit einem Schnee-Rabbid zu erschrecken. / Als ein Rabbid versehentlich ein Pinguin-Ei zerbricht, will er es ersetzen.
programme.sub-title: Der Weihnachts-Rabbid // Der Schnee-Rabbid // Der einmalige Eier-Rabbid

programme.title: SpongeBob Schwammkopf
programme.desc: Der Winter bricht in Bikini Bottom an und Sponge und Patrick nutzen das für eine Schneeballschlacht. Thaddäus geht der damit verbundene Lärm natürlich auf den Zeiger.

programme.title: The Loud House: Weihnachten bei den Louds
programme.desc: Die Weihnachtsferien haben begonnen und die Louds freuen sich auf ein schönes Fest. Doch leider landet beim Rodeln Lincolns Schlitten im Garten des griesgrämigen Nachbarn Mr. Grouse. Kann sich Lincoln seinen geliebten Schlitten zurückholen?

programme.title: Bucket & Skinner's Epic Adventures: Superweihnachten
programme.desc: Buckets jährlicher Familienausflug zu Weihnachten ist ins Wasser gefallen. Das drückt die Stimmung gewaltig. Doch als Bucket einschläft, trifft ihn eine Überraschung...

programme.title: A Rainha do Natal
programme.desc: Ashley Mackenzie encontra Ben, um recém-chegado que também ama o feriado. Vendo-o como rival no início, ela percebe que juntos podem criar um Natal ainda mais especial, unindo forças e celebrando o verdadeiro espírito natalino.

programme.title: Romance De Natal Arranjado
programme.desc: A Mandy descobre uma copia velha de "Um Conto de Natal" de Charles Dickens e uma carta de 70 anos para Papai Noel junto com uma moeda de muito valor.

programme.title: O Esquadrão do Papai Noel
programme.desc: Allie, uma professora de arte desempregada, aceita um trabalho no Esquadrão do Papai Noel para ajudar um viúvo rico e suas filhas a redescobrirem a magia do Natal. Enquanto tenta animar o espírito natalino, Allie é recompensada com o amor.

programme.title: Tocam Sinos
programme.desc: Uma família com pouco dinheiro se preocupa em não poder comprar presentes um para o outro, até receber um pouco de inspiração de uma lenda do Natal.

programme.title: Uma Viagem Para Paris
programme.desc: Lucas, um rico empresário francês, vai a Montana para uma proposta de negócio muito atraente. Lá, ele conhece Robin, se apaixona e a leva para Paris em uma incrível aventura de Natal. Mas será que os negócios acabarão com esse romance?

programme.title: Um conto de fadas nas Montanhas: Entrando para a realeza
programme.desc: É Natal novamente e a Dra. Tasha está a caminho para encontrar o Príncipe Alexander em St. Savarre.

programme.title: O Natal de James & Bob
programme.desc: Um músico de rua em dificuldades se vê alvo de uma investigação de bemestar animal que ameaça levar seu amado gato no Natal.

programme.title: Um Conto De Fadas Nas Montanhas
programme.desc: A pediatra Tasha Mason está focada em manter as crianças de sua enfermaria o mais saudáveis possível. Mas quando o belo Príncipe Alexander Cavalieri quebra a perna em uma pista de esqui, Tasha é forçada a cuidar de um mimado membro da realeza.

programme.title: Uma Estrela no Paraíso
programme.desc: Quando um empreiteiro ameaça a vida pacífica de Noelle, ela e seus amigos usam seu dom de fazer milagres para frustrar seus planos e salvar seu vilarejo.

programme.title: Anjo de Natal
programme.desc: Ashley se sente sozinha no Natal enquanto procura um emprego. Seu vizinho Nick lhe oferece um emprego de assistente no melhor trabalho: ajudar os outros. Há uma coisa que ela não pode contar a ninguém que seu novo chefe é uma espécie de Papai Noel secreto

programme.title: Uma Canção de Natal
programme.desc: Charlotte é nova na cidade e acontece que sua mãe tornou-se íntima do pai de quem parece que ela se tornará sua pior inimiga.

programme.title: It's Christmas Again
programme.desc: La víspera de Navidad cambia dramáticamente para Jake Young cuando un accidente de patineta lo transporta a Belén la noche del nacimiento de Jesús.

programme.title: La navidad de Jonathan
programme.desc: Cuando un niño pierde el belén de madera que lo vincula con su padre muerto, su madre preocupada convence a un tallador de madera solitario y malhumorado para crear un reemplazo y permitir que su hijo lo vea trabajar en él

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: La Navidad de James & Bob
programme.desc: James Bowen es objeto de una investigación sobre el bienestar de los animales que amenaza con llevarse a su amado gato, Bob, en Navidad.

programme.title: Una estrella en el paraíso
programme.desc: Nacida bajo una estrella navideña, Noell cree que tiene un don para realizar milagros e influir positivamente en las personas que la rodean.

programme.title: Lucía y el Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucía es la primera niña en la Escuela Internacional de Natal. Cuando acusan a su mejor amigo Oscar de robar el cristal mágico del Rey del Invierno, que alimenta la máquina actual, Lucía se propone demostrar su inocencia.

programme.title: Un ángel en mi vida
programme.desc: Con la ayuda del Arcángel Gabriel (Dean Cain), Angelina se embarca en una misión casi imposible, tratar de salvar a su malcriada hija de 14 años, Ravin Foxworth, de ir por el camino equivocado.

programme.title: El Deseo de Charlie
programme.desc: Un veterano militar regresa a casa después de estar ausente por estrés postraumático. Con su nuevo perro, descubre en medio de la Navidad un nuevo propósito en su vida: ayudar a los exmilitares que necesitan ayuda

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.

programme.title: It's Christmas Again
programme.desc: La víspera de Navidad cambia dramáticamente para Jake Young cuando un accidente de patineta lo transporta a Belén la noche del nacimiento de Jesús.

programme.title: La navidad de Jonathan
programme.desc: Cuando un niño pierde el belén de madera que lo vincula con su padre muerto, su madre preocupada convence a un tallador de madera solitario y malhumorado para crear un reemplazo y permitir que su hijo lo vea trabajar en él

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: La Navidad de James & Bob
programme.desc: James Bowen es objeto de una investigación sobre el bienestar de los animales que amenaza con llevarse a su amado gato, Bob, en Navidad.

programme.title: Una estrella en el paraíso
programme.desc: Nacida bajo una estrella navideña, Noell cree que tiene un don para realizar milagros e influir positivamente en las personas que la rodean.

programme.title: Lucía y el Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucía es la primera niña en la Escuela Internacional de Natal. Cuando acusan a su mejor amigo Oscar de robar el cristal mágico del Rey del Invierno, que alimenta la máquina actual, Lucía se propone demostrar su inocencia.

programme.title: Un ángel en mi vida
programme.desc: Con la ayuda del Arcángel Gabriel (Dean Cain), Angelina se embarca en una misión casi imposible, tratar de salvar a su malcriada hija de 14 años, Ravin Foxworth, de ir por el camino equivocado.

programme.title: El Deseo de Charlie
programme.desc: Un veterano militar regresa a casa después de estar ausente por estrés postraumático. Con su nuevo perro, descubre en medio de la Navidad un nuevo propósito en su vida: ayudar a los exmilitares que necesitan ayuda

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.

programme.title: It's Christmas Again
programme.desc: La víspera de Navidad cambia dramáticamente para Jake Young cuando un accidente de patineta lo transporta a Belén la noche del nacimiento de Jesús.

programme.title: La navidad de Jonathan
programme.desc: Cuando un niño pierde el belén de madera que lo vincula con su padre muerto, su madre preocupada convence a un tallador de madera solitario y malhumorado para crear un reemplazo y permitir que su hijo lo vea trabajar en él

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: La Navidad de James & Bob
programme.desc: James Bowen es objeto de una investigación sobre el bienestar de los animales que amenaza con llevarse a su amado gato, Bob, en Navidad.

programme.title: Una estrella en el paraíso
programme.desc: Nacida bajo una estrella navideña, Noell cree que tiene un don para realizar milagros e influir positivamente en las personas que la rodean.

programme.title: Lucía y el Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucía es la primera niña en la Escuela Internacional de Natal. Cuando acusan a su mejor amigo Oscar de robar el cristal mágico del Rey del Invierno, que alimenta la máquina actual, Lucía se propone demostrar su inocencia.

programme.title: Un ángel en mi vida
programme.desc: Con la ayuda del Arcángel Gabriel (Dean Cain), Angelina se embarca en una misión casi imposible, tratar de salvar a su malcriada hija de 14 años, Ravin Foxworth, de ir por el camino equivocado.

programme.title: El Deseo de Charlie
programme.desc: Un veterano militar regresa a casa después de estar ausente por estrés postraumático. Con su nuevo perro, descubre en medio de la Navidad un nuevo propósito en su vida: ayudar a los exmilitares que necesitan ayuda

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.
